# Spectify — environment configuration
#
# This monorepo contains two independently configured services.
# Each has its own .env.example — copy the relevant one(s) to .env
# in the directory where you run the process:
#
#   packages/orchestrator/.env.example   — spectifyd (orchestrator daemon)
#   packages/reports/.env.example        — spectifyr (reports service)
#
# The spectify CLI (spectify) has no .env file; it is configured via:
#   spectify config set <key> <value>    (stored in ~/.spectify/config.json)
#
# Shared variable (affects all three processes when set in the environment):
#   SPECTIFY_HOME=~/.spectify            — base directory for all runtime data
